<Algorithm code="           1. If _length_ &gt; 2&lt;sup&gt;32&lt;/sup&gt; - 1, throw a *RangeError* exception.           1. If _proto_ is not present, set _proto_ to %Array.prototype%.           1. Let _A_ be MakeBasicObject(« [[Prototype]], [[Extensible]] »).           1. Set _A_.[[Prototype]] to _proto_.           1. Set _A_.[[DefineOwnProperty]] as specified in &lt;emu-xref href=&#34;#sec-array-exotic-objects-defineownproperty-p-desc&#34;&gt;&lt;/emu-xref&gt;.           1. Perform ! OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(_A_, *&#34;length&#34;*, PropertyDescriptor { [[Value]]: 𝔽(_length_), [[Writable]]: *true*, [[Enumerable]]: *false*, [[Configurable]]: *false* }).           1. Return _A_.         ">
   <head>
      <AbstractOperationHead isHostDefined="false" name="ArrayCreate" retTy="either a normal completion containing an Array or a throw completion" id="sec-arraycreate" virtualPackage="10 Ordinary and Exotic Objects Behaviours.4 Built-in Exotic Object Internal Methods and Slots.2 Array Exotic Objects.2 ArrayCreate ( length [ , proto ] )" location="https://tc39.es/ecma262/2025/">
         <params>
            <NormalParam name="length" ty="a math value"/>
         </params>
         <params>
            <OptionalParam name="proto" ty="an Object"/>
         </params>
      </AbstractOperationHead>
   </head>
   <body>
      <BlockStep>
         <block>
            <StepBlock>
               <steps>
                  <SubStep directive="null">
